{{infobox Chinese|l=Yang Water Dog|kanji=壬戌|romaji=mizunoe inu|onyomi=jinjutsu|p=rénxū|w=jen-hsü|mi=ʐən³⁵ ɕy|y=jam4 seot1|j=jam4 seot1|ci=jɐm sœt̚|mc=ɲiɪm syt|oc-bs=ɲɨm ʔsuʔ}}
{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yang Water Dog also known as <!--please transliterate all the hiragana readings into romaji and provide the kanji--> Jinshitsu''' (壬戌) (みずのえいぬ、じんすいのいぬ、じんじゅつ) is one of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|干支}}.

It is the 59th combination in the Sexagenary cycle; the preceding one is {{ill|Xinyou|ja|辛酉}} and the following one is {{ill|Guihai|ja|癸亥}}. In the system of {{ill|Yin-Yang and the Five Elements|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin-Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行}}, the {{ill|Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}}’ {{ill|Ren|ja|壬}} represents yang {{ill|Water|ja|水}}, while the {{ill|Twelve Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}}’ {{ill|Inu|ja|戌}} represents yang {{ill|Earth|ja|土}}, and they are in the relationship of {{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=Mutual Restraint|lt_ja=相剋}} (Earth overcomes Water).

== Years of Jinshitsu ==
A year in the {{ill|Common Era|ja|西暦}} that leaves a remainder of 2 when divided by 60 is a {{ill|Year|ja|年}} of Jinshitsu.
