{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive|qq=}}
'''Yang Water Dog also known as  Jinshitsu''' (壬戌) (みずのえいぬ、じんすいのいぬ、じんじゅつ) is one of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|干支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}.

It is the 59th combination in the Sexagenary cycle; the preceding one is {{ill|Xinyou|ja|辛酉|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} and the following one is {{ill|Guihai|ja|癸亥|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}. In the system of {{ill|Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin-Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}’ {{ill|Ren|ja|壬|1=Mizunoe (壬)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} represents yang {{ill|Water|ja|水|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, while the {{ill|Twelve Earthly Branches|1=Earthly Branches|lt=Twelve Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}’ {{ill|Inu|ja|戌|1=Dog (zodiac)|lt=Dog (戌)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} represents yang {{ill|Earth|ja|土|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, and they are in the relationship of {{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=Mutual Restraint|lt_ja=相剋|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} (Earth overcomes Water).

